
        This tool helps capture the screen using hotkeys.&nbsp; It will automatically store the images to disk after capture.</p>
    <h2>
        Capturing</h2>
    <p>
        The defined hotkeys are Shift-PrtScn, Ctrl-PrtScn, and Shift-Ctrl-PrtScn.<br />
        <table class="style1">
            <tr>
                <td>Shift-PrtScn</td>
                <td>Capture the entire desktop, and save it to a file.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ctrl-PrtScn</td>
                <td>Capture the current top-level window, and save it to a file.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ctrl-Shift-PrtScn</td>
                <td>Allow the region or window to be picked by either clicking on a window with the mouse, or dragging the mouse to select a region.</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <p>
            The temporary directory must be set before using the application.</p>
